<h1>To William Cocks and John Ashby</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">To Captain William Cocks, of the first Company of Rangers; and Captain John Ashby, of the Second Company.</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">[27 October 1755]</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>You are hereby ordered, to remain with your Companies at George Parkers Plantation, where you are to erect a Stockade Fort; in building of which, you are to follow Lieutenant Bacons Instructions; he being sent to direct and plan the same.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> As this is intended for the protection of the Country People, there is no doubt but they will assist all in their power, especially in providing Tools which, without, you may meet with some difficulty. If Lieutenant Bacon should apply for an Escort to conduct him to Captain Ashbys Company, or to any other place, to which it may be dangerous travelling withoutyou are to see that he is allowed it: you are to send a trusty Sergeant with proper powers &amp;c. for Recruiting, in order to complete your Company. You are to be very careful to see that no irregularities are committed by your Company, that strict Discipline is observed, and that great pains be taken to inculcate morality and good Harmony, among the Men.</p>
<p>You are to build Barracks therein for your men, and a Magazine for the Reception of the Stores which are to be sent hither: also, to receive necessaries for your own Company.</p>
<p>You are to collect all the Publick Arms and Horses, which you may hear of in the parts adjacent to you, and secure them until
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-02-02-pb-0142">[142]</span>
they are called for. You are to transmit me the first day of every month, a particular Return of the State of your Company, relating to the variations that may have happened; as also an exact account of your proceedings since your last Return.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> Besides these, you are to send me a weekly Return, signed by yourself and Officer, of the State of your Company. You are to provide yourself upon the most reasonable terms, with such Tools as you find absolutely necessary to carry on the work. You are to receive provisions for immediate use, according to my order at Pearsalls;<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> and you will hereafter be supplied from this Fort with what you want. By return of the Waggons which came up with Major Lewiss party, you will receive about eight hundred weight of Flour;<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0004-ptr">4</a> and of that you are to be particular in seeing no waste is committed &amp;c.</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">G:W.</p>
</div>
<div class="postscript">
<p>N:B. Captain Ashbys Company is stationed at Sellars and McCrackins; at the direction of Lieutenant Bacon.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p><a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0139" class="document">GW gave John Bacon on 26 Oct.</a> specific instructions for building the two forts. See also <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0149" class="document">GW to Bacon, 28 Oct. 1755</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>John Ashbys return of 21 Oct. for the 2d company of rangers gave the names of 33 men, the first of whom had been recruited on 18 Aug. William Cocks on the same day listed 24 men; the first was not recruited until 1 Sept.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-02-02-0133" class="document">GW to William Cocks, to John Ashby, 23 Oct. 1755</a>, both written from Pearsals.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-02-02-0144-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>GW was at Fort Cumberland on 26 Oct. when he instructed assistant Commissary Allan McLean to provide Ashby with 1,200 weight of flour and Cocks with 800. The reference to eight hundred weight of Flour suggests that it was the letter sent to Cocks rather than the one to Ashby which was copied in the letter book and is printed here.</p>

</div>
</div>
